http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Students-from-northeastern-States-to-visit-Dharwad-Belagavi/article14002348.ece

A 28-member team of students from northeastern States will tour different places in Dharwad and Belagavi districts from Monday to Thursday.It is part of a programme titled ‘Students Experience in Inter-State Living’.InitiativeIt is an initiative by the Akhil Bharatiya Vidyarthi Partishad (ABVP) to promote national integration. Mayor Ashwini Majjagi would receive the team at the railway station here on Monday, ABVP State secretary T.S. Sunil Prasad said at a press conference here on Saturday.ABVP started this initiative to bridge the gap between border areas and other parts of the country.Visits to institutionsOn Tuesday, the team would visit different industrial, educational and folk cultural institutions and interact with the heads and staff. A public reception would be accorded to the team at B.T. Auditorium at B.V.B. College of Engineering and Technology in the evening.KLE Technological University Vice-Chancellor Ashok Shettar, Hubballi-Dharwad Commissioner of Police Pandurang H. Rane would take part, he added.The team would visit Belagavi district on Wednesday and Thursday, Mr. Prasad said.